The paper deals with efficient algorithms for linear algebraic problems, such as solving linear systems and recovering spectral approximations of matrices. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.DS and cs.NA seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on algorithmic techniques for solving linear algebraic problems efficiently. The use of sparsification and semidefinite programming techniques also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the cs.CG and cs.LG categories. Finally, the application of the results to graph theory and network analysis suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.SI category.
